contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Mianserin is a tetracyclic antidepressant that has antihistaminic and hypnosedative but almost no anticholinergic effect It is a weak inhibitor of norepinephrine reuptake and strongly stimulates the release of norepinephrine Interactions with serotonin receptors in the central nervous system have also been found Its effect is usually noticeable after one to three weeks Mianserin may cause drowsiness and hematological problems
